<br />
Sorry Llan, I didnt quit, yet. The account IS cancelled atm, my Enchanter is still active though, and resides in PoK. Ill restate my previous quote to say 'a majority' of players will be leaving for EQ2 and WoW in a few months, instead of totally. Because thats what is happening right now, a majority of players are leaving. Its not affecting all servers, but where Im at, my guild is 99% WoW now, and the high level players able to do OoW zones like MPG or RS successfully for group purposes, are non-existant. Its worse on the PvP servers, because SoE totally botched what they said theyd fix after implementing the first round of changes to the PvP environment (reward system, penalties).
<br />

<br />
If you asked a few months ago if I believed SoE would change their tune, Id have given you a thumbs up in support. But Ive waited, and waited, and its always the response of "under evaluation" and "no change planned at this time" I hear. Now if people wanna enjoy EQ1, and can, by all means do it, but Im not going to get blind-sided by a few meager changes and start thinking "OMG THEY CAREZ ABOUTZ US". 
<br />

<br />
Im looking at this from the point of view of someone whose played this dirty game of cat n mouse with SoE for 5 years, and cant fathom why I deluded myself into thinking, every year, it would get better, when it really got worse. And yea if I went to a summit, thats the exact attitude Id be taking. Not the "Im really enjoying EQ1 right now what will you do to improve it," attitude, but the "Im not enjoying EQ1 right now, at all, what will you do to retain my attention/subscription" attitude. Those are the type of people you need to send to a summit. If you constantly surround yourself with people who agree all the time, you end up believing your own BS, and thats whats ultimately happening with SoE and these summits.
<br />

<br />
Til the players come home, wait for the changes, and get disappointed.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
