                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The last time I remember having any fun in EQ was when I was helping a ranger with her epic 1.5 or something like that.   I tend to get a rush from wondering if I had enough mana to keep mezzing or will I die a painful death from the mobs.  That was fun.
<br />

<br />
After that, I pretty much stalled at lvl 67, and I haven't really bothered to go back.  I can't handle just standing there in a group, mindlessly nuking or casting the random buff on the group to just have something to do.  Sure, I could mezz if I had the spells from OoW, but when you get turned down because you don't have a certain mezz, you're pretty much out of luck.  
<br />

<br />
At that point, I had to start asking for my replacement because I was too bored to do that crap over and over again. 
<br />

<br />
I do know I will not play EQ2 at all.  It's not worth the aggravation dealing with a company who has a proven poor customer service, mind you, we're discussing SoE, not Sony as a whole.  Also, their "ticket" system feels more like the lottery to me.  You win if you can get a GM to respond within two days.
<br />

<br />
Either way, I chose WoW to spend my time on.  It allows me to do one of the things we've been calling for a long time in EQ....the ability to actually enchant items.  It's not the only reason I'm playing, but I can't deny my roots. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
My guild is pretty diverse as well.  Not only does Pak'Cafan have a presence in EQ, we're in WoW, eq2, DaoC, and maybe a couple others.  Unfortunately, it's come down to the point where quite a few are leaving because EQ is too much of a time sink.  They want to raid, but the people don't have the time to plan, set up, and attend the raid, especially when it comes to anything after Time.   EQ had either become a chore for them, or they were burnt out from the constant raiding.
<br />

<br />
Gonna stop here before I go all night long.  But I chose WoW because it's more flexible to my schedule then say....EQ right now.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
