                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">At this point, expecting anything from Summits or SoE is pretty much delusional, to say the least.
<br />

<br />
Thus, my question is not "What will SoE do for us?", but more like "When is SoE going to merge servers?"
<br />

<br />
I know right now it is Christmas time and stuff, but ever since EQ2 and WoW came out I find this at prime time:
<br />

<br />
PoK - 40 peeps (this has been going on for months now, not just after EQ2 release)
<br />
WoS - 2 Groups exping 
<br />
MPG - 1 or 2 Groups exping 
<br />
KT - Empty.
<br />
Bazaar - 200+ Traders.
<br />
RSS - 1 group or empty (Got 2 RSS invites so far, as 70 chantie or bard since OOW release)
<br />
MPG Trials - 2 invites since OOW release.
<br />

<br />
As for high-end raiding, most guilds are lucky if they have 50 peeps at raid, when they raid.
<br />

<br />
This applies for MT server, but I am sure there are other servers just like it.
<br />

<br />
The biggest problem I see right now is not what is SoE going to nerf/break next, but how long is LFG going to be up today. 
<br />

<br />
Nowadays, if I only have 1 hour of play time, I dont bother logging because of the LFG downtime, or if I log I certainly dont put LFG up and just solo some AAs with my bard in PoN.
<br />

<br />
SoE needs to fix the LFG downtime. Ever since PoP they made LFG downtime increase expansion after expansion, for group requirements were getting tighter and tighter in order to be able to even exp grind. And I consider myself lucky because I chose to play a chanter and bard, which are a more group desirable classes to play than most. However, my necro and mage have had their share of LFG downtime, less an issue with necro since I would solo while LFGing for hours, but solo and all it does get old.
<br />

<br />
Thus again, <span style="font-weight: bold">"When is SoE going to merge servers?"</span>
<br />

<br />
Or better yet, <span style="font-weight: bold">"When is SoE going to allow FREE server transfers for their loyal customer base that didnt get the benefit of an extended 30-days FREE subscription because we never left in the first place?"</span>
<br />

<br />
As for SoEs focus for the last 6 months, Ill share my own insight. When  competition was lurking around the corner (WoW) SoE did the following:
<br />

<br />
1- Splitting GoD expansion into 2 different expansions (GoD and OOW), and delaying the level 70 cap raise for the 2nd part of GoD expansion (called OOW), which will be released much closer to WoW release time as an attempt to retain players busy with leveling by the time WoW comes live. Releasing as a result a level 70 planned expansion for level 65s, making GoD pretty much unplayable for most.
<br />

<br />
2- For the first time ever, organize a marketing stunt called Summit, to communicate the idea of "SoE will care for its customers from now on". Which remained as an idea, since the compromises they made were never really intended to be fulfilled and haven't been to date.
<br />

<br />
3- Give a 30-day come back FREE month to those who left, so that they get hooked again on EQ and dont buy WoW.
<br />

<br />
4- Release the 2nd part of GoD expansion (OOW), which among other niceness makes all the focus items people worked their butts off getting (Elemental, Time, and even the 2 month old expansion ones) obsolete, in hopes that people will stick around and rebuilt all their focus items with OOW, as well as leveling their characters to 70 and do some more AAs, instead of buying WoW.
<br />

<br />
5- Release EQ2 with little to none testing a week before WoW went live in order to capitalize in all those who left the game or are thinking about trying a new game, so that when WoW comes out, most of them just bought a new game, EQ2, and dont buy WoW.
<br />

<br />
Did all these actions make EQ a better game overall game-play quality wise? No, actually it had the opposite effect.
<br />

<br />
Was SoE thinking about making EQ a more fun game to play for the last 6 months? Certainly not.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Just in case SoE is listening (ROFL), you are a tricksie one, but your trickery didnt work. All WoW copies are sold out, to the point that Blizzard has announced they will not put more copies into the market till they upgrade their servers to be able to absorb the masses, Christmas and all. OMFG!! They are willingly losing money on the behalf of making their game more quality wise enjoyable. Imagine THAT!
<br />

<br />
Here is my advice to you SoE (again, ROFL), do NOTHING! Just give us, YOUR customers that STILL pay the monthly fees to play YOUR game, a 30-day FREE Server transfer. That way you can have all your ghost servers still running while keeping in denial about the low subscriptions and server populations. Chances are, if you do merge the serves, you will screw it up anyways. Also, by letting the customers move freely for a month (up to whatever population limit you set) we will not be able to BLAME you!</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Manizeh on Mon Dec 13, 2004 5:40 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
