                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I believe that server merges now would be the most detrimental thing that SOE could possible do to the game.
<br />

<br />
Right now there is a very obvious drop in population, the result of other games (several of them), American holiday season, and general nerfage.  Some guilds are getting 25% turnout; others are claiming no impact.  Numbers in PoK are down, numbers in Bazaar on my server are at roughly 40% of pre-Omens numbers.
<br />

<br />
Before Omens, people were constantly complaining about server over-population - crowded zones, competition for raid targets, etc, and asking when a new server would be added.
<br />

<br />
However, there have been drops before, which have always recovered.  We can't be sure that there is a real drop in populations until probably mid-February.  If there are mergers, and the population recovers even a very small amount, most servers would end up worse off than before.
<br />

<br />
Some people will say that they need action now, or else more will leave.  Well, there are plenty of things that you can do yourself right now.  Try guild alliance for raid targets, or just dropping your sights for a bit.  For groups, try recruiting lower level people (who have always been complaining about getting groups), and going to a spot where they can be effective.  Etc.
<br />

<br />
There is one exception where I think server merges should be considered - the Zeks.  There are issues there with conflicting playstyles, so I don't look forward to the fallout from that at all.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
