                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">At this day and age, I sincerely doubt people that left EQ for EQ2 or WoW will ever come back to EQ. I also acknowledge peeps having not interest in EQ2 or WoW and keep playing EQ.
<br />

<br />
And about servers merging being bad... I guess it is ok to do so for a price, of lets say 75$ for server transfer for each account?
<br />

<br />
If I were SoE I would consider non active accounts as not accontable for server population, and either move an entire server to another one with same low active accounts population, or just give a 30-day FREE server transfer to active accounts and let the players relocate themselves (unless they hit whatever max population they set).
<br />

<br />
Else, EQ will end up as a collection of ghost servers with soloers due to LFG downtime.
<br />

<br />
And if people come back after 6 months or 1 year, and their server is currently full, they could give them a choice of servers not maxed yet to join instead. Chances are their friends are gone and their guild disbanded anyways.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
